# AlphaSwarm Worker Agent Model
# Register with: ollama create alphaswarm-worker -f modelfiles/Modelfile.worker
#
# Base: qwen3.5:35b (36B MoE, ~3B active) — model decision 2026-06-11.
# Benchmarked on this M1 Max 64GB (ollama 0.30.7, llama.cpp Metal path):
#   qwen3:8b  (old worker): prefill 422 t/s, decode 43 t/s
#   qwen3.5:35b (this):     prefill 833 t/s, decode 60 t/s — faster AND
#   two model generations smarter. Dense-model parallel decode is memory-
#   bandwidth-capped on M1 Max (4-way qwen3:8b aggregated only ~25-43 t/s),
#   so a fast MoE single-stream beats a parallel dense 8B outright.
# Known limitation: qwen35moe arch serializes decode under OLLAMA_NUM_PARALLEL
# in 0.30.7 (same family as ollama issues #14510/#14621/#14879). Prefill
# still overlaps; NUM_PARALLEL=4 stays set (harmless, helps other archs).
# MLX upgrade path: rebase on qwen3.5:35b-a3b-nvfp4 (MLX backend, ~2x
# prefill) once benchmarked — requires OLLAMA_USE_MLX=1 (configure script).
FROM qwen3.5:35b
PARAMETER num_ctx 4096
PARAMETER temperature 0.7
PARAMETER num_gpu 999
# Decision JSON is ~100-150 tokens; 400 caps pathological repetition loops
# (the 14-20 min/call tail observed in the 41.3 smoke) at zero quality cost.
# Re-register after editing: ollama create alphaswarm-worker -f modelfiles/Modelfile.worker
PARAMETER num_predict 400
